  <subsection xml:id="subsec-Code-clap">
    <title>Code</title>
    <term>Source Code</term>
    <program >
int soundSensor=2;//declare sensor
int LED=4;.//led declaration
boolean LEDStatus=false;
void setup() {
pinMode(soundSensor,INPUT);//mode declaration for sensor
pinMode(LED,OUTPUT);//mode declaration for LED
}
void loop() {
int SensorData=digitalRead(soundSensor); //Get data from the sensor
if(SensorData==1){
if(LEDStatus==false){
  LEDStatus=true;//set status =true
  digitalWrite(LED,HIGH);//set led as high
  }
  else{
  LEDStatus=false;//set status =false
  digitalWrite(LED,LOW);//set led as low
  }
  }
  }  
    </program>
    <term>Code explanation </term>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Initialize the pin of the sensor to the 2nd pin of the Arduino, Longer of the LED is connected to the 4th pin of the Arduino.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Initially the variable LED is set to false 
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          In void setup(), declaring the sensor pin as input using Pinmode function and LED pin as output using Pinmode function
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          In void loop (), when the sensor detects any sound it activates LED to on by itself.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
